    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>in half lengthways, then wash thoroughly to remove any grit from between the leaves</p><p>Top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/easy-one-pot-haddock-and-leek-risotto/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leek </strong>and<strong> shallot</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/easy-one-pot-haddock-and-leek-risotto/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the leek softens, dissolve your <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock mix</strong> in 750ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[975ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [1.4L]</span><strong> boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/easy-one-pot-haddock-and-leek-risotto/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> to the pan along with your <strong>arborio rice </strong>and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat the grains in the butter</p><p>Add the <strong>stock</strong> a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 25-30 min or until all of the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Tip: Add a splash more water if it's looking a little dry!</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/easy-one-pot-haddock-and-leek-risotto/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>dill </strong>finely</p><p>Zest your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> (try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter)</p><p>Season your <strong>haddock bites</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Tip: Unevenly sized haddock bites? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/easy-one-pot-haddock-and-leek-risotto/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is tender with a slight bite, stir through the juice of <strong>half</strong> the<strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>lemon[s]</strong>, your <strong>soft cheese</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>lemon zest</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>dill</strong> (save the rest for garnish!)</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/easy-one-pot-haddock-and-leek-risotto/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top the rice with the <strong>haddock bites</strong> and cook, covered, for 4-5 min further or until the haddock is cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>one pot haddock & leek risotto</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/easy-one-pot-haddock-and-leek-risotto/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>one pot</strong> <strong>haddock & leek risotto </strong>garnished with a <strong>lemon wedge</strong>, the <strong>remaining lemon zest</strong> and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped dill</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of<strong> black pepper </strong>and a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
